Voting and representation were also reshaped under the banner of integrity. Trump announced that his lawyers were drafting an executive order to eliminate mail\uc0\u8209 in balloting nationwide, citing a conversation with Vladimir Putin and repeating the false claim that mail\u8209 in voting had \'93rigged\'94 the 2020 election. Mail\u8209 in ballots were used by nearly a third of Americans and had not been credibly linked to widespread fraud. Eliminating them would disproportionately affect voters who relied on the mail\'97seniors, people with disabilities, rural residents, and those with inflexible jobs. In Texas, Governor Greg Abbott signed a new congressional map that could raise Republican seats from 25 to 30 out of 38, despite the state\'92s growing diversity. Civil rights groups and the NAACP sued, arguing that the map diluted Black and minority voting power in violation of the Voting Rights Act. In Missouri, the governor called a special session to redraw districts in a way that could add another Republican seat and to tighten rules on citizen\u8209 led ballot initiatives. The ground rules of representation were being rewritten.\
